      {
        "id": "docling_book_en_5.Advanced.Modern.Algebra.-.J.Rotman.2003_page_572_9",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Theorem 8.47 (Maschke's Theorem). If G is a finite group and k is a field whose characteristic does not divide |G|, then kG is a left semisimple ring.",
        "bbox": [
          0.20488721967418538,
          0.44040697671834966,
          0.7932330641594938,
          0.4694940474208045
        ],
        "order": 10
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_book_en_5.Advanced.Modern.Algebra.-.J.Rotman.2003_page_572_10",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Remark. The hypothesis always holds if k has characteristic 0.",
        "bbox": [
          0.20676692801625834,
          0.49127907041451296,
          0.6635338229235914,
          0.504464285789293
        ],
        "order": 11
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_book_en_5.Advanced.Modern.Algebra.-.J.Rotman.2003_page_572_11",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Proof. By Proposition 8.42, it suffices to prove that every left ideal I of kG is a direct summand. Since k is a field, kG is a vector space over k and I is a subspace. By Corollary 6.49, I is a (vector space) direct summand: There is a subspace V (which may not be a left ideal in kG) with kG = 1 @ V. There is a k-linear transformation d : kG → 1 with d(b) = b for all b € I and with ker d = V [each u € kG has a unique expression of the form u = b + v, where b € I and v € V, and d(u) = b]. Were d a kG-map, not merely a k-map, then we would be done, by the criterion of Corollary 7.17: I is a summand of kG if and only if it is a retract; that is, there is a kG-map D: kG → I with D(u) = u for all u € I. We now force d to be a kG-map by an \"averaging\" process.",
        "bbox": [
          0.20300751849121207,
          0.5188492062105247,
          0.793233091369666,
          0.6526162785690459
        ],
        "order": 12
      },
